    • Method Detail

      • getServiceURL

        public static final java.lang.String getServiceURL(ConfigureInterface configInfo)
        Try to get 'data service URL' from
        1. system property PROPERTY_SERVER_URL
        2. item ITEM_SERVER_URL of section SECTION_NAME from configuration.
        If not found, then try to get the 'protocol', 'host', 'port' and 'baseName' by
        1. PROPERTY_PROTOCOL, PROPERTY_HOST, PROPERTY_PORT and PROPERTY_BASE_NAME from system property
        2. ITEM_PROTOCOL, ITEM_SERVER_URL, ITEM_HOST, ITEM_PORT from configuration
        and concatenate them into a URL as protocol+host+":"+port+"/"+baseName

        Parameters:
        configInfo - ConfigureInterface, the configuration to find ITEM_SERVER_URL, ITEM_HOST, ITEM_PORT etc.
        Returns:
        String, the SAFS data service URL.

        public static boolean isInterceptStep()
